        "title": "Name it to tame it",
        "body": "Once you can say it out loud — \"I get defensive when I feel blamed\" — the trigger loses its grip.\n\nNaming it turns an ambush into something you saw coming. Now you can plan: take a breath, ask a question, step away for a minute. The reaction is automatic. The response is yours — **if** you see the trigger first."
