        "body": "Frustration feels like a reason to quit. It's actually a sign you **care** and you've hit an edge — the place where growth happens.\n\nSo don't read it as \"I'm failing.\" Read it as \"time to change strategy or push.\" Same energy, pointed forward.\n\nAnd when even that runs low: discipline carries you. Motivation gets you started; **habits keep you going** on the days you feel nothing."
